URL = http://ksenya.cryptoacademy.org/

=Description=

"It is not about cryptography and math as such, P2P technology, about Trustless Transactions and distributed consensus systems that can be built using public key cryptography.

The aim is to look at design of these systems and try to formulate it in words, not in code, as it usually is and by looking at exisitng projects and concepts and Difference Between them.

Bitcoin is already explained pretty well in non technical terms - but there are other infrastructures involving public key cryptography which have other features and related to Decentralisation."
(http://ksenya.cryptoacademy.org/view/welcome-visitors/view/rebooting-global-economy)

